---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Borrow Our Talent" description="Fractional access to Microsoft-certified AI specialists embedded with your healthcare team, on your schedule, at a scope that fits your organization.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner page-hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-badge">Borrow</div>
        <h1>Borrow Our AI Talent</h1>
        <p>You can't hire a Power Platform developer to a rural health center. You can't justify a full-time BI analyst on an FQHC budget. But you still need the work done. Scale Street's Borrow services give you fractional access to Microsoft-certified AI specialists, embedded with your team, on your schedule, for as long as you need them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-image">
        <img src="/images/team-collaboration.jpg" alt="Team collaboration on healthcare projects" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How Borrow Works -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner how-works">
      <p>Borrow is not project-based consulting. It's not a one-time engagement where someone builds a thing and disappears. It's ongoing, embedded access to a specialist who learns your workflows, your data, your people, and becomes a part of how your organization operates.</p>
      <p>Think of it as hiring the person you need without the recruiting, onboarding, or benefits overhead.</p>
      <div class="feature-list">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-check">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span>A dedicated specialist (not a rotating team of junior consultants)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-check">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span>Predictable monthly engagement with defined hours</span>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-check">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span>Healthcare-specific expertise (we only work in healthcare)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-check">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span>Microsoft-certified team (Power BI, Power Platform, Copilot, M365)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-check">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span>Flexible terms (no long-term lock-in required to start)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Borrow Roles -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Borrow Roles</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="roles-grid">
        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="card-accent blue"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Fractional Chief Transformation Officer / Chief AI Officer</h3>
            <p>For organizations that need senior leadership to define and drive their AI strategy. Your fractional CTO/CAIO assesses organizational readiness, builds an AI adoption roadmap, aligns AI initiatives with strategic priorities, advises executive leadership and the board, and ensures your AI investments deliver measurable outcomes. This is the person who owns the "why" and the "what" so your team can focus on the "how."</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> FQHCs and rural hospitals that lack a senior technology or innovation leader, organizations preparing for Rural Health Transformation Program initiatives, and networks looking for strategic guidance across their member organizations.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request This Role <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="card-accent green"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Fractional AI Project Manager</h3>
            <p>For organizations that have AI initiatives underway (or about to launch) but no one dedicated to managing them. Your fractional PM coordinates deployments, manages timelines and stakeholders, tracks adoption metrics, removes blockers, and keeps AI projects moving. Whether it's a Copilot rollout, a Power Platform build, or a training program, your PM makes sure it actually gets done.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> Organizations juggling multiple AI or technology projects without dedicated project management capacity. Especially valuable during Copilot deployments, Power Platform implementations, or RHT-funded technology initiatives.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request This Role <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="card-accent mint"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Fractional AI Analyst</h3>
            <p>For organizations drowning in spreadsheets, manual reporting, and underused tools. Your fractional analyst builds Power BI dashboards, automates UDS and quality reporting, configures Copilot workflows, develops Power Automate processes, and turns your data into decisions. No more pulling reports by hand. No more month-end scrambles. No more paying for tools nobody uses.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> FQHCs that need UDS reporting modernized, rural hospitals that want real-time operational dashboards, organizations with low Copilot adoption, and networks that need standardized reporting across member organizations.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request This Role <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card bundle">
          <div class="card-accent peach"></div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="bundle-badge">Recommended</div>
            <h3>Comprehensive Bundle</h3>
            <p>For organizations that need more than one of the above, or that want a single fractional technology partner covering strategy, project management, and hands-on analytics. The Comprehensive Bundle gives you a coordinated team that owns your entire AI adoption effort from roadmap to execution.</p>
            <div class="card-meta">
              <span class="best-for">Best for:</span> Organizations going through a technology modernization or those preparing for the Rural Health Transformation Program's technology initiatives.
            </div>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Let's Design a Bundle <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Network Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="network-grid">
        <div class="network-content">
          <h2>Shared Fractional Talent Across Your Network</h2>
          <p>PCAs and HCCNs can contract Borrow services on behalf of multiple member organizations. A single Fractional BI Analyst can serve several health centers in a network, building standardized dashboards and reporting across all of them, at a per-organization investment that none of them could justify alone.</p>
          <p>This is one of the most efficient ways to close the AI talent gap at scale. Your network provides the coordination. We provide the talent.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Design a Network Borrow Program <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
        </div>
        <div class="network-visual">
          <img src="/images/community-health.jpg" alt="Health center network collaboration" class="network-image" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="section-inner faq-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How quickly can a specialist start?</summary>
          <p>Most engagements begin within 2-3 weeks of contract signing. We match you with a specialist based on your specific needs and tech stack.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do we need to have Power BI / Power Platform / Copilot already?</summary>
          <p>Not necessarily. If you have Microsoft 365, you likely have access to many of these tools already. We'll help you assess what's included in your current licensing and what (if anything) you'd need to add.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can we start with one role and add more later?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. Many organizations start with a single specialist and expand as they see results.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What if we need more hours than a standard engagement?</summary>
          <p>The Comprehensive Bundle covers expanded scope. For anything beyond that, we'll design a custom engagement.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is there a minimum commitment?</summary>
          <p>We recommend a 3-month minimum to see meaningful results, but we don't require long-term contracts to get started. The work speaks for itself.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How much does it cost?</summary>
          <p>Engagements are scoped to your organization's size, needs, and hours required. Let's have a conversation and we'll put together a proposal that fits your budget.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="section-inner section-center">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Not sure what role you need?</h2>
        <p>Most organizations know they have a gap. They just aren't sure what to call it. Tell us what's not working, and we'll recommend the right fit.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Schedule a Conversation <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .page-hero-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-green);
    background: rgba(9, 92, 68, 0.07);
    padding: 0.375rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .page-hero p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  /* How Borrow Works */
  .how-works {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .how-works > p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-list {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.875rem;
  }

  .feature-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.875rem;
  }

  .feature-check {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(9, 92, 68, 0.08);
    color: var(--color-green);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .feature-item span {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* Shared */
  .bg-light {
    background: var(--color-gray-50);
  }

  .cta-section {
    background: var(--color-gray-50);
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* Role Cards */
  .roles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .role-card {
    display: flex;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    border-radius: 16px;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .role-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .role-card.bundle {
    border-color: var(--color-peach);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--color-peach);
  }

  .card-accent {
    width: 6px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .card-accent.blue { background: var(--color-blue); }
  .card-accent.green { background: var(--color-green); }
  .card-accent.mint { background: var(--color-blue-light); }
  .card-accent.peach { background: var(--color-peach); }

  .card-body {
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .card-body h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .card-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .best-for {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .bundle-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-brown);
    background: rgba(255, 149, 99, 0.1);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Network */
  .network-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .network-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .network-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .network-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 360px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .faq-item summary:hover {
    color: var(--color-blue);
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: "+";
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    content: "−";
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: -0.25rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 3.5rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;
    }

    .page-hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .page-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      height: 260px;
    }

    .network-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .network-image {
      height: 240px;
    }
  }
</style>
